        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512131" appearance="hottext">Kit Part No. 1698264C1 (3S8139A)</hotlnk>
                </title>
                <figure id="f9512131" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512131.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Kit Part No. 1698264C1 (3S8139A)</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is not necessary to remove the charge air cooler to install the mounting brackets.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the clamps and hoses between the horns on the charge air cooler and the inlet
                        and exhaust tubes.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove radiator tank mounting bolts as follows:</para>
                    <para>
                        <title>Left/Drivers Side</title>
                    </para>
                    <para>On the rear side of the radiator tank flange, remove the 2nd and 3rd mounting bolts down from
                        the top corner (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512131">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Save the lockwashers and nuts.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <title>Right/Passenger Side</title>
                    </para>
                    <para>On the rear side of the radiator tank flange, remove the 1st and 2nd mounting bolts down from
                        the top corner (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512131">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Save the lockwashers and nuts.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Mount the brackets as follows:</para>
                    <para>
                        <title>Left/Drivers Side</title>
                    </para>
                    <para>Position the left hand bracket over the left horn on the charge air cooler as illustrated in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512131">Figure 1</hotlnk>. The bracket will mount to the outboard side of the
                        radiator tank; the clamping tabs should face inboard.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <title>Right/Passenger Side</title>
                    </para>
                    <para>Position the right hand bracket over the right horn on the charge air cooler as illustrated in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512131">Figure 1</hotlnk>. The bracket will mount to the inboard side of the
                        radiator tank; the clamping tabs should face inboard.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Before tightening the bolts, make sure the beads on both horns of the charge air cooler
                            are positioned in the openings in the clamps as illustrated in
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9512131">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Fasten both brackets to the side of the radiator tank with 5/16 inch - 18 x 1-1/2
                        inch bolts. Re-use the 5/16 inch nuts and lock washers removed above. Install bolts so that the
                        bolt heads are on the inboard side of the flange. Tighten to 215 to 265 in-lbs. (24 to 30 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install one 3/8 inch - 16 x 3/4 inch clamping bolt and 3/8 inch flat washer through
                        the mounting surfaces of both brackets as illustrated in Figure 1. Tighten to 30 to 38 ft-lbs.
                        (41 to 51 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install a 3/8 inch - 16 x 1 inch bolt and 3/8 inch flat washer in the clamping tab
                        on each bracket. Tighten to 30 to 38 ft-lbs. (41 to 51 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Re-install both hoses and clamps between the charge air cooler and the inlet and
                        exhaust tubes.
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512132" appearance="hottext">Kit Part No. 1698265C1 (3S8138A)</hotlnk>
                </title>
                <figure id="f9512132" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512132.webp" type="webp" resolution="150"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Kit Part No. 1698265C1 (3S8138A)</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is not necessary to remove the charge air cooler to install the mounting brackets.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the clamps and hoses between the horns on the charge air cooler and the inlet
                        and exhaust tubes.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">On both ends of the radiator, remove the 1st, 2nd and 3rd radiator tank to header
                        bolts as illustrated in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512132">Figure 2</hotlnk>. Save the lock washers and nuts.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the mounting brackets over both charge air cooler horns with the clamping
                        tabs facing inboard and the bracket mating with the outboard side of the radiator tank (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512132">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Before tightening the bolts, make sure the beads on both horns of the charge air
                                cooler are positioned in the openings in the clamps as illustrated in
                                <hotlnk xrefid="f9512132">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Fasten both brackets to the outboard side of the radiator tank flange (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512132">Figure 2</hotlnk>) with 5/16 inch - 18 x 1-1/2 inch bolts. Reuse the
                        5/16 inch nuts and lock washers removed above. Install bolts so that the bolt heads are on the
                        inboard side of the flange. Tighten to 215-265 in-lbs. (24-30 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install a 3/8 inch -16 x 1 inch bolt and 3/8 inch flat washer in the clamping tab on
                        each bracket (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512132">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Tighten to 30-38 ft-lbs. (41-51 Nm).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Re-install both hoses and clamps between the charge air cooler and the inlet and
                        exhaust tubes.
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
